{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "It uses six approaches to aggregate passage-level signals for a long document: 1) PARADE Avg: adopting average pooling for the passage representations of a long document to obtain the final document representation, where this is similar to CEDR [112]; 2) PARADE Sum: performing additive pooling across passage representations; 3) PARADE Max: using element-wise max pooling for all passage representations to obtain the representation of the final document; 4) PARADE Attn: adopting a feedforward network to generate an attention weight for each passage; 5) PARADE CNN: generating pairs of passage representations using several convolutional neural networks (CNNs) until only one remains; and 6) PARADE Transformer: aggregating passage representations through two randomly initialized transformer encoders.",
    "To obtain context-aware passage-level signals, Wu et al.",
    "introduced the passage-level cumulative gain model (PCGM) to rank documents [154].",
    "In their model, BERT was first applied to obtain passage-level [CLS] representations, following which they were aggregated via LSTM [5].",
    "3.3.2 Ranking Strategies via BERT."
  ],
